.TH CODEVAR 1 "January 2026" "codevar 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codevar \- generate encoded variable using secret and text
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B codevar
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITEXT\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcodevar\fR generates encoded variables using a secret key and text input.
The mechanism combines the secret (optionally protected with year) with the
text, encodes it using a base encoding scheme, and trims to the specified
length.
.PP
Mechanism:
  secret' = digest(yyyy + SECRET + yyyy)  (when -y flag is used)
  result = trim(encode(secret' + TEXT + secret'), length)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-secret=\fR\fISECRET\fR
Secret key to use.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-length=\fR\fILEN\fR
Trim output to length (default: 8).
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-digest=\fR\fIDGST\fR
Digest algorithm (default: sha256).
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-year\fR
Protect secret with year around: yyyy + SECRET + yyyy.
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-encode=\fR\fIENCODE\fR
Encoding method (default: base64).
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-base64\fR
Use base64 encoding.
.TP
\fB\-8\fR, \fB\-\-base85\fR
Use base85 encoding.
.TP
\fB\-9\fR, \fB\-\-base91\fR
Use base91 encoding.
.TP
\fB\-B\fR, \fB\-\-base122\fR
Use base122 encoding.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Default values can be defined in \fB~/.config/codevar/config.ini\fR:
.PP
.RS
.nf
secret=SECRET
length=LEN
digest=DGST
encode=ENCODE
.fi
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate encoded variable with secret:
\fBcodevar\fR \fB\-s\fR "mysecret" "hello world"
.TP
Use year protection:
\fBcodevar\fR \fB\-s\fR "mysecret" \fB\-y\fR "hello world"
.TP
Use base91 encoding with custom length:
\fBcodevar\fR \fB\-s\fR "mysecret" \fB\-9\fR \fB\-l\fR 12 "hello world"
